reviewText: My daughter and I loved True Jackson when it was on Nickelodeon, and we are thrilled to have it on DVD.  We bought all 3 seasons and would have a True Jackson "marathon" to reward ourselves when we would get a project done or her room picked up!  Love, love, LOVE this show!
My daughter was so happy to get this in the Mail. It played perfectly and we received it quickly. It matched the exact description that was advertised.
Product was sent promptly and in good shape. I wish it had been the entire season one But they can only ship what they have. All in  all. Nice doing business with you. Thanks!
I love watching this show and I'm glad I got it on DVD. It is really funny and it kind of reminds me of The Nanny a little bit. I just hope volume 2 comes soon. Great show and great DVD.

Let's face it, Other than SpongeBob SquarePants, Nickelodeon shows haven't been that great since Taina was personally canceled by Nick in 2002. Especially ones marketed to teens or with teen actors, - Drake & Josh was a Kenan & Kel rip-off. Unfabulous, iCarly and Zoey 101 seem to be more aimed towards little kids than teens. I have yet to see another Nickelodeon Non-cartoons since 2003 up until this show have not been anywhere near on the same level as Salute Your Shorts, All That, Kenan & Kel or Clarissa Explains It All. And While I still do not consider this show on the same page as those, It's pretty close Then in 2008 comes True Jackson, VP - a show about 15 year old True Jackson (KeKe Palmer), who is hired to be the Vice President (Hence the title) of youth apparel Mad Style - a fashion and clothing company, after The owner notices and like True's modifications to one of his designs she's wearing. Anyone who liked 90s Nickelodeon might like this show. It's a HUGE improvement over what Nick has given us since 2003
True Jackson VP is the best  show ever.  Whenever I am feeling down True Jackson is there to make me laugh like crazy! Truly Hilarious
My daughter got this DVD for Christmas. She never saw the show before and neither did. But I bought it based on the star, Keke Palmer. My daughter loves this show and has been watching it non-stop.

I thought this was supposed to be True Jackson VP compete season 1 but it is not. It is mission many episodes from season 1. The episodes it is missing are: Company Retreat, Switcheroo, True Intrigue, Amanda Hires a Pink, Max Mannequin, True's New Assistant, House Party, Back to School Testing True, True Crush, The Hotshot, The Wedding and The Dance. Where is the True Jackson VP Season 1 Volume 2 DVD? I can't find it anywhere on the internet.

My daughter watches the shoes over and over again. I am happy they are available.

This was the second time getting this movie. The first time the disc's were loose in the case and scratched up. The second time the case was broken on inside and 1 if the disc's were scratched up but playable.  It was also delivered to my neighbor instead of me.

Some people may have had a different experience then me, but I ordered True Jackson VP Season 1, Volume 1. The discs were supposed to be in "New" condition, but it's hard to say if it actually was new or not. The order was fulfilled by Amazon, but it came from another seller. I could immediately tell that that the set had been repackaged and there was a sticker on it that said the name of the set and the word "NEW" on it. I still wasn't bothered by this, but the case had also been replaced as it's supposed to come in a clear case to be able to read the inner cover and instead it was in a typical black dvd case. Still not a big deal for me. I was even able to get passed the slash in the barcode. Some factories do that to their liquidated stock. What bothered me was that this set comes with two dvds and they were both shoved into a single disc case with one disc bumping around freely. I kept the set because I have plenty of empty double-disc cases around and just switched it out. I just wanted others to be aware that this is what some people are considering to be "New" condition. The dvds in the set are great though and well produced. I'm happy I got them, just not how I got them.
this show is surprisingly funny and this dvd set is great! It's just a shame it doesn't include more episodes.
